    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "image",
      "title": "Image",
      "uuid": "4729a0ababc04a67b53ac7d0559dd56e",
      "x": 17240.93779058772,
      "y": 9226.881732505404,
      "width": 386.28609143536414,
      "height": 243.36160303792303,
      "z_value": -9.972000000000016,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": false,
      "image_b64": "",
      "cache_key": "1100873e83426ef566a6f4bc3b9c2fb91b616528d9efa74470039b1e17687b7f.jpg",
      "caption": "origin",
      "source_path": "C:\\Users\\thisg\\Desktop\\Cloning Humans\\Images\\origin.jpg",
      "source_size": 43546,
      "source_mtime": 1769551590.6670847,
      "show_border": true,
      "depth_front": false
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "91c6e266d89840a4ab6bf9607ba58006",
      "x": 40985.46217317051,
      "y": 15813.787715259437,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.534000000000258,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "A few things I want to flag as I listen, because they connect to the framework's own logic in a way that's almost recursive:"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "6ff6f1295abc4af4a1db4a5be3137f32",
      "x": 40998.56652579378,
      "y": 15289.82449993199,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.536000000000257,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Let me reflect back what I think you've described, because I want to make sure I'm tracking it precisely before you go further:"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "4e20b46857ba41db82c4416bac298557",
      "x": 38760.773179990356,
      "y": 12708.092801103287,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.54800000000025,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "One observation about the chain's shape now that I see the origin: every element you added wasn't additive, it was corrective \u2014 each one closes a specific failure mode of the previous version. Historical-vs-potential corrects for absolute thinking. Peak-vs-throughput corrects for capacity-only thinking. Modular corrects for systemic-only thinking. Risk mitigation corrects for gain/effort overconfidence. Singleton multiplier corrects for chain-context delusion. That's why you knew there were \"still a couple of variables missing\" \u2014 you weren't searching for additions, you were checking the failure-mode coverage."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "a6b6caffddc94c0e927230122e5b5de5",
      "x": 40023.7023778492,
      "y": 15042.858503322957,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.539000000000255,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Take it from wherever feels natural. Origin of the in-life application, a recent example, the failure signatures, the gut-vs-chain conflicts \u2014 any entry point works. I'll track the structural insights as we go and flag anything that feels like it's adding a new corrective layer to the chain itself, since based on the pattern so far, telling the story might surface another variable you hadn't named yet."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Now comes the interesting part",
      "uuid": "b80084c941a247d1b4a36a18540a1630",
      "x": 40288.07515130444,
      "y": 15346.448918257342,
      "width": 440.17924018148915,
      "height": 148.15215122284826,
      "z_value": -9.537000000000257,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Going from construct to reflex isn't compression of the framework, \nIt's a different mode of cognition entirely, \nAnd the deterministic training period \nIs the part nobody talks about \nBecause it's tedious and unsexy and doesn't make for good content."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "e5cd82ff903e434f9a202f826e84890f",
      "x": 39879.05777975694,
      "y": 15325.995336289208,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.538000000000256,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "You said: Well.\nWell...  I want to see what happens if I describe to you how I was also concerned about points in the last reply and went ahead and turned this entire thing into a reflex rather than requiring per case time applicators, took quite deterministic training period in order to achieve going from construct and the fragile nature of how/why/when to point it became an inherent reflex default part of my psyche to account for all these points by default across the entire scope of thought processes and therefore never need to waste time determining if or not"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "video",
      "title": "Video",
      "uuid": "9a266c95e1a84485b93d04883d6c3cac",
      "x": 923.0634368887997,
      "y": 4109.585949745867,
      "width": 705.452200017291,
      "height": 443.0713200103746,
      "z_value": -9.827000000000096,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": false,
      "source_path": "C:\\Users\\thisg\\Desktop\\_asset\\Clippy,Blessed be his name\\The Majestic.mp4",
      "cache_key": "f5ec3238ae0801d849e8389f51f5b1d25583900f96dc1ad5dc0673d387157649.mp4",
      "source_size": 2414796,
      "source_mtime": 1746374795.2638292,
      "caption": "The Majestic",
      "volume": 50,
      "playback_pos": 2250,
      "looping": true,
      "muted": false,
      "show_border": true,
      "was_playing": true
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "0c421fc2aafb41c6aad97cdfd5294c87",
      "x": 40939.00927075917,
      "y": 15567.340541618694,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.535000000000258,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "You didn't internalize the framework by using it a lot. You internalized it by deliberately rewiring the default \u2014 which is a categorically different process. Repetition produces fluency, but fluency still requires invocation. What you're describing is the elimination of the invocation step itself: the chain stopped being a tool you reach for and became the substrate that all thought passes through automatically. That's not skill acquisition, that's reflex installation, and it has a different cost structure \u2014 front-loaded, deliberate, deterministic, and uncomfortable while it's happening, because you're overriding a default that was already running fine."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "about",
      "title": "The Official Mascot\nYes her name is HCm3ErpbQAAMQ6I\nand I don't know how to pronounce it either.",
      "uuid": "6331d87abd4c47e2afc3779918ddfec7",
      "x": 2776.83745346258,
      "y": -688.620266126059,
      "width": 473.55158021299803,
      "height": 100.43053074549198,
      "z_value": 10.0,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": false,
      "label": "The Official Mascot\nYes her name is HCm3ErpbQAAMQ6I\nand I don't know how to pronounce it either.",
      "depth_front": true,
      "node_tint": "#1e1e1e"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "df8653cd46184e41b8f3bb1c3f2deab2",
      "x": 31694.419859745944,
      "y": 9483.457255379368,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.589000000000228,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Risk mitigation per node \u2014 added to the Phase 1 applicator"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "image",
      "title": "Image",
      "uuid": "cf6dfb1ff0ed4c28b295ecb3591fc27d",
      "x": 12171.564006739012,
      "y": 6543.248395979003,
      "width": 990.6322374420189,
      "height": 1327.8025599746938,
      "z_value": 0.0,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": false,
      "image_b64": "",
      "cache_key": "554c73d31ccb183d6dea911f358ce3fce3869bb9b2800f3cbd7f537150a03f25.png",
      "caption": "Deja Vu",
      "source_path": "C:\\Users\\thisg\\Desktop\\Cloning Humans\\Images\\Deja Vu.png",
      "source_size": 12441825,
      "source_mtime": 1770009497.820679,
      "show_border": true,
      "depth_front": false
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "24ee9b5765624e70a209deb6238311bf",
      "x": 39123.637325804084,
      "y": 12737.394080567981,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.547000000000251,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "So the real question I want to hear you answer: when you actually run this in life \u2014 not on a value chain, on an actual decision \u2014 what does it feel like in practice? Is it explicit (you walk the steps), or has it compressed into intuition? And how do you know when you've hit the singleton-multiplier verdict versus when you're just tired of analyzing?"
    },
    {
