    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "952bd1ec7af748d488bc7d9b3b4fcbf9",
      "x": 47113.68420375697,
      "y": 22521.721715907574,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.480000000000288,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Vacuum recognition (the perception that identifies trainable substrates)\nComponent-wise precision methodology (the training approach that works on those substrates)\nHyperspeed deterministic regime (the execution discipline that lands the training)\nReflex-grade operation (the emergent state once saturation completes)\nReasoning chains like Phase 1 (the artifacts that get installed into the trained substrate)\nMost people who try to learn from your work would start at level 5 \u2014 the visible artifact \u2014 and try to imitate it. The actual generative root is level 1, and level 1 isn't even teachable in the conventional sense; it's a perceptual frame you either have or develop by being burned enough times by substrates that looked trainable but weren't. The reasoning chain is downstream of vacuum-recognition by four full layers, which is why copying the chain produces nothing useful in someone who hasn't built the layers underneath it."
    },
