    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Oh, I have been doing lovely, thanks for asking",
      "uuid": "18149bac30db4c3f856e64b15eef742c",
      "x": 7532.861486082047,
      "y": 2263.6941932454897,
      "width": 509.92301489503916,
      "height": 248.00146356778123,
      "z_value": -9.426000000000318,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "  Just been busy playing with some toys and stuff\nAww, that sounds fun! \ufffc  What kind of toys have you been playing with lately? Are we talking fun gadgets, hobby stuff, video games, or something else entirely?  Spill the details \u2014 I\u2019m genuinely curious! \n\nWhat\u2019s been your favorite one so far?\n\nThe 50 thousand line interactive transparency nodal tree that absorbs any app agnostic of SDK or architectural framework and just outran the qt event loop while mass processing a live cartesian data flow.\n\nThat is not a toy. That\u2019s a goddamn kaiju!  "
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "about",
      "title": "And considering things of times passed is a regression mentality",
      "uuid": "312df3481b1940b4b432f2b94304e0fb",
      "x": -336.59906013890406,
      "y": -658.0840481506784,
      "width": 669.0625,
      "height": 31.0,
      "z_value": -9.959000000000023,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": false,
      "label": "And considering things of times passed is a regression mentality",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "about",
      "title": "We had to come up with a Deployment system",
      "uuid": "e2ab01c4d87840a9b401eb1eae0a96d7",
      "x": 16589.005500072613,
      "y": 9598.99955938872,
      "width": 451.453303351399,
      "height": 34.15517286479053,
      "z_value": -9.977000000000013,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": false,
      "label": "We had to come up with a Deployment system",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": "#2a3a2f"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "0c263dd2f7f544a08edcba9e533f4a70",
      "x": 32088.87595620025,
      "y": 9679.889691206163,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.588000000000228,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "For each node (and each interface), the profile now also captures:"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "Sweetums Cookies",
      "uuid": "a9aa4b1cf6e045d6910317a671eb1401",
      "x": 1865.9385685591478,
      "y": -624.9355845054846,
      "width": 362.96460890224785,
      "height": 291.28470908886055,
      "z_value": -10.0,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "There is a famous phrase that women use in certain groups \"Don't be a wife to a boyfriend\".  It just means you shouldn't be giving your all to people who don't really care that much about you.\n\nBut the fact of the matter is that dudes have a similar thing, just not an official slogan like the women do.  So like, what that other woman over there is trying to do is get wife privileges without even being a girlfriend.\n\nI'm not quite sure how to feel about that.\n\nThat's just not a thing for random humans, and then you stalk me around because I'm nice to my spouse thinking you will get the same... what the heck is wrong with your head?"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "about",
      "title": "We have come a long way\nStill the same typewriter\nStill the same features\nStill the same energy\nIt evolved",
      "uuid": "ab1b9449b6184744953fb789eb3487c2",
      "x": 5473.962792123635,
      "y": 3849.6298355831686,
      "width": 330.78888845729307,
      "height": 155.29802818756247,
      "z_value": -9.844000000000086,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": false,
      "label": "We have come a long way\nStill the same typewriter\nStill the same features\nStill the same energy\nIt evolved",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": "#2a3a2f"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "claude_response",
      "title": "Response",
      "uuid": "95091975813c4d5faa7fed2cb48f875f",
      "x": 15170.476851660453,
      "y": -21.679417846164142,
      "width": 420.0,
      "height": 232.0,
      "z_value": -9.745000000000141,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "label": "All 23 icons rebuilt with layers up to 256px, and `iconSize` now matches `iconButtonSize` at 48px \u2014 icons fill edge to edge with no padding shrinkage. PlayStation-dominant.",
      "depth_front": false,
      "node_tint": ""
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "462b648e46e1484da0992def1dd57f68",
      "x": 26444.7770639005,
      "y": 945.6674216134243,
      "width": 289.4981483844749,
      "height": 115.985187075785,
      "z_value": -9.629000000000206,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Then identify chain practices required per each link/node in the overall route we have discussed so far"
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "warm",
      "title": "",
      "uuid": "5a30ca81638e47e199c79a6da2e17601",
      "x": 26990.71400150211,
      "y": 1249.4365880675082,
      "width": 300.0,
      "height": 200.0,
      "z_value": -9.627000000000207,
      "ports_visible": false,
      "shelf_visible": true,
      "body_text": "Historical population growth \u2014 measured against potential growth per context Key idea: compare actual trajectories to what was theoretically possible given each era's constraints (food, disease, tech, geography, social structure). The gap = the interesting part.\nPrimary goods and services \u2014 future demand vs. current daily peak demand, then vs. supply chain daily average load Key idea: project future demand for essentials and benchmark against today's peak-load capacity (not averages). Then compare those load-bearing limits against the supply chain's daily average load \u2014 not the goods' own average load. The supply chain itself is the binding constraint.\nMap to top 10 destination hotshots + estimated handling times per each Key idea: overlay the demand/supply picture onto the busiest destination hubs. Estimate handling time per hub to localize where throughput bottlenecks concentrate.\nIdentify chain practices required per link/node along the full route Key idea: walk the end-to-end route built so far (origin \u2192 supply chain \u2192 top-10 destination nodes) and specify the operational practices each link/node needs to sustain the modeled load \u2014 handling, storage, transfer, scheduling, redundancy, etc. Turns the diagnostic into a prescriptive playbook per node.\nReady for the next."
    },
    {
      "node_id": 0,
      "node_type": "about",
      "title": "The only known photo of Eddie",
      "uuid": "8112a5dffac44d92994348dd8e7261b2",
